HEADWORD: Odmyl
<hw>Od"myl</hw> <pr>(⟦ocr⟧d"m⟦icr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>"odmh`</grk>, <grk>"osmh`</grk>, stench + <ets>-yl</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A volatile liquid obtained by boiling sulphur
with linseed oil. It has an unpleasant garlic odor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Odocoileus</ent>⟦br⟧
